<subSubSection pageId="75" pageNumber="966" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="75.[113,754,1629,2069]" lastBlockId="75.[813,1451,189,245]" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,217,1629,1653]" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Remarks</emphasis>
. Three species are now recognised in 
<taxonomicName authority="Serene &amp; Soh, 1970" authorityName="Serene &amp; Soh" authorityYear="1970" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[640,754,1629,1653]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Bresedium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Serene &amp; Soh" box="[113,359,1661,1685]" firstAuthor="Serene" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" pagination="387 - 416" refId="ref76461" refString="Serene R &amp; Soh CL (1970) New IndoPacific genera allied to Sesarma Say 1877 (Brachyura, Decapoda, Crustacea). Treubia, 27: 387 - 416." type="journal article" year="1970">Serène &amp; Soh, 1970</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="(De Man, 1889)" baseAuthorityName="De Man" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[375,711,1661,1685]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipes">
<emphasis box="[375,508,1661,1685]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">B. brevipes</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="De Man" box="[527,704,1661,1685]" firstAuthor="De Man" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" pagination="409 - 452" refId="ref72218" refString="Man JG De (1889) Ueber einige neue oder seltene indopacifische Brachyuren. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abteilung fur Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Thiere, Jena, 4 (2): 409 - 452, pls. 9, 10." type="book chapter" year="1889">De Man, 1889</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Tweedie, 1940)" baseAuthorityName="Tweedie" baseAuthorityYear="1940" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sediliense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">B. sediliense</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Tweedie" box="[238,406,1693,1717]" firstAuthor="Tweedie" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" pagination="88 - 113" refId="ref78385" refString="Tweedie MWF (1940) New and interesting Malaysian species of Sesarma and Utica (Crustacea, Brachyura). Bulletin of the Raffles Museum, 16: 88 - 113, figs. 1 - 12, pl. 24." type="journal article" year="1940">Tweedie, 1940</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Li, Shih &amp; Ng, 2019" authorityName="Li, Shih &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2019" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eurypleon">
<emphasis box="[479,620,1693,1717]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">B. eurypleon</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Li, Shih &amp; Ng" firstAuthor="Li" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" pagination="21" refId="ref77087" refString="Shih H-T, Hsu P-Y, Shahdadi A, Schubart CD &amp; Li J-J (2019) The synonymy of the supratidal crab species Parasesarma cognatum Rahayu &amp; Li, 2013 with P. liho Koller, Liu &amp; Schubart, 2010 (Decapoda: Brachyura: Sesarmidae) based on morphological and molecular evidence, with a note on P. paucitorum Rahayu &amp; Ng, 2009 Zoological Studies 58: 21. doi: 10.6620 / ZS. 2019.58 - 21, pp. 1 - 13." type="journal article" year="2019">Li, Shih &amp; Ng, 2019</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tweedie" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[239,481,1725,1749]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sediliense">
<emphasis box="[239,481,1725,1749]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Bresedium sediliense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only one known from the Sunda Shelf, and its generic position is not certain, although it does have a characteristic male pleon which has the telson distinctly sunken into the distal margin of somite 6 and the tip of the distal chitinous part of the G1 flared. 
<bibRefCitation author="Li" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Li" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" refId="ref71682" refString="Li J-J, Shih H-T &amp; Ng PKL (2020) The Taiwanese and Philippine species of the terrestrial crabs Bresedium Serene and Soh, 1970 and Sesarmops Serene and Soh, 1970 (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura), with descriptions of two new species. Zoological Studies, 59: 16. doi: 10.6620 / ZS. 2020.59 - 16, 32 pp." type="book" year="2020">Li et al. (2020)</bibRefCitation>
revised the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serene &amp; Soh" authorityYear="1970" box="[382,498,1886,1909]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Sesarmops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[382,498,1886,1909]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Sesarmops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[554,752,1885,1909]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[554,668,1885,1909]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Bresedium</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[179,263,1917,1941]" name="Taiwan" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[278,404,1917,1941]" name="Philippines" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, and Sulawesi and commented on the problems with the two genera. They showed that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Rathbun" baseAuthorityYear="1914" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philippinense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">B. philippinense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="De Man" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[625,744,1981,2005]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipes">
<emphasis box="[625,744,1981,2005]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">B. brevipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; recognised a new species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li, Shih &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2019" box="[408,548,2013,2037]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eurypleon">
<emphasis box="[408,548,2013,2037]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">B. eurypleon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with a diagnostic G1 structure with an elongate distal chitinous part; described a new species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serene &amp; Soh" authorityYear="1970" box="[1016,1135,190,213]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Sesarmops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1016,1135,190,213]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Sesarmops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li, Shih &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2020" box="[1156,1245,190,213]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Sesarmops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mora">
<emphasis box="[1156,1245,190,213]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">S. mora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); and redescribed 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Rathbun" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[813,1097,221,245]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Sesarmops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" sensu="stricto" species="mindanaoensis">
<emphasis box="[813,1097,221,245]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Sesarmops mindanaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1105,1165,222,245]" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="75.[813,1452,285,693]" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">
<bibRefCitation author="Serene &amp; Soh" box="[813,1068,285,309]" firstAuthor="Serene" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" pagination="387 - 416" refId="ref76461" refString="Serene R &amp; Soh CL (1970) New IndoPacific genera allied to Sesarma Say 1877 (Brachyura, Decapoda, Crustacea). Treubia, 27: 387 - 416." type="journal article" year="1970">Serène &amp; Soh (1970)</bibRefCitation>
noted that both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serene &amp; Soh" authorityYear="1970" box="[1275,1399,286,309]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Sesarmops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1275,1399,286,309]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Sesarmops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serene &amp; Soh" authorityYear="1970" box="[813,927,317,341]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[813,927,317,341]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Bresedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were related in having the male telson sunken into the distal margin of somite 6. They separated 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serene &amp; Soh" authorityYear="1970" box="[1336,1451,350,373]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Sesarmops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1336,1451,350,373]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Sesarmops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as having a more trapezoidal carapace versus a rectangular carapace for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serene &amp; Soh" authorityYear="1970" box="[960,1076,413,437]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[960,1076,413,437]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Bresedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Ongoing studies now show that neither the carapace shape, nor the male telson are reliable characters at the generic level. Both genera are very close, and some species now placed in these genera do not possess the distinctive telson-somite 6 feature. There are also several kinds of G1 structures present, and it is clear that a full revision of both genera will be needed. This is beyond the scope of the present paper and will have to be undertaken at a future time.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="75.[813,1452,733,1206]" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">
For the present work, only one species is treated as it had been placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Serene &amp; Soh" authorityYear="1970" box="[1036,1206,765,789]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Pseudosesarma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1036,1206,765,789]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Pseudosesarma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
previously— 
<taxonomicName authority="Zehntner, 1894" authorityName="Zehntner" authorityYear="1894" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Sesarma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="edwardsi" variety="laevimana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Sesarma edwardsi</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[967,1078,797,821]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">laevimana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zehntner" box="[1086,1249,797,821]" firstAuthor="Zehntner" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" pagination="135 - 214" refId="ref78899" refString="Zehntner L (1894) Crustaces de l'Archipel Malais. Voyage de MM. M. Bedot et C. Pictet dans l'Archipel Malais. Revue Suisse de Zoologie et Annales du Musee d'Histoire Naturelle de Geneve, 2: 135 - 214, pls. 7 - 9." type="journal article" year="1894">Zehntner, 1894</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
—and we find that it is actually a senior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Tweedie, 1940)" baseAuthorityName="Tweedie" baseAuthorityYear="1940" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sediliense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Bresedium sediliense</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Tweedie" box="[933,1099,861,885]" firstAuthor="Tweedie" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" pagination="88 - 113" refId="ref78385" refString="Tweedie MWF (1940) New and interesting Malaysian species of Sesarma and Utica (Crustacea, Brachyura). Bulletin of the Raffles Museum, 16: 88 - 113, figs. 1 - 12, pl. 24." type="journal article" year="1940">Tweedie, 1940</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Specimens from Lorentz River in New 
<collectingCountry box="[906,985,893,917]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Guinea</collectingCountry>
which have been identified as “ 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Sesarma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevimana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Sesarma laevimana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” in NMBA are here identified as a new species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schubart &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2020" box="[844,963,958,981]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Migmarma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[844,963,958,981]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Migmarma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schubart &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2020" box="[978,1096,957,981]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Migmarma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lorentzi">
<emphasis box="[978,1096,957,981]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">M. lorentzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see later). The placement of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tweedie" baseAuthorityYear="1940" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sediliense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">B. sediliense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serene &amp; Soh" authorityYear="1970" box="[961,1076,989,1013]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[961,1076,989,1013]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Bresedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as presently diagnosed is mainly because of the male telson being prominently sunken into the distal margin of somite 6 and the G1 having the distal chitinous part elongate. In the phylogenetic tree (
<figureCitation box="[1356,1439,1085,1109]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="91.[113,149,1757,1779]" captionTargetBox="[116,1448,352,1737]" captionTargetId="figure-15@91.[86,1475,347,1749]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="Fig. 59. Phylogenetic relationships among selected taxa of Sesarmidae (91 OTUs), including all representatives of Chiromantes and Pseudosesarma previous to current revision of these genera. In addition, several species of Bresedium and Sesarmops are considered, as the revision also involves some of their former members. Topology and confidence values were determined by means of a phylogenetic reconstruction based on 1,096 basepairs of mtDNA (16S-tRNALeu-ND1), conducted with MrBayes, GTR+I+G as substitution model, and Parasesarma plicatum as outgroup (midpoint rooting). Posterior probabilities were determined after 4 million generations with a burn-in of 25%. All species so far classified within Chiromantes (without obvious anterolateral teeth) are shaded in blue, whereas those species that used to be classified in Pseudosesarma (carrying at least one pair of anterolateral teeth) are shaded in yellow." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5351405" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5351405/files/figure.png" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tweedie" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[813,948,1117,1141]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sediliense">
<emphasis box="[813,948,1117,1141]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">B. sediliense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not part of but adjacent to the main clade of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serene &amp; Soh" authorityYear="1970" box="[813,927,1149,1173]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[813,927,1149,1173]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Bresedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serene &amp; Soh" authorityYear="1970" box="[985,1101,1150,1173]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Sesarmops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[985,1101,1150,1173]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Sesarmops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although the bootstrap support is not considered strong enough to be definitive.
</paragraph>
